95. Discuss the purpose and functionality of PHP sessions and outline their potential application in maintaining a user's shopping cart state across multiple pages.
ANSWER
Purpose of PHP Sessions
 PHP sessions are used to store user-specific data on the server, allowing you to maintain state across multiple pages (HTTP is stateless by default).
They help:
 Track user activity (e.g. login status)
 Store temporary data (e.g. shopping cart, form data)
 Maintain state during a browsing session

Functionality of PHP Sessions

1.Session Start
  Use session_start() to begin or resume a session. It must be the first thing on the page:
Eg:session_start();

2.Storing Data
 Session variables are stored in the $_SESSION superglobal array:
Eg:$_SESSION['username'] = 'Alice';

3.Accessing Data
 On any other page (after session_start()), you can access:
Eg:echo $_SESSION['username']; // Output: Alice

4.Ending a Session
 To clear or destroy a session:
Eg: session_unset();    // Remove all session variables
    session_destroy();  // Destroy the session

Using PHP Sessions to Maintain a Shopping Cart
<?php
session_start();
// Handle add to cart
if (isset($_GET['add'])) {
    $product = $_GET['add'];

    // Initialize cart if not set
    if (!isset($_SESSION['cart'])) {
        $_SESSION['cart'] = [];
    }
   // Add product to the cart
    $_SESSION['cart'][] = $product;
    $message = "$product has been added to your cart.";
}
// Handle clear cart
if (isset($_GET['clear'])) {
    unset($_SESSION['cart']);
    $message = "Cart has been cleared.";
}
?>
<!DOCTYPE html>
<html>
<head>
    <title>PHP Shopping Cart with Sessions</title>
</head>
<body>
    <h1>Simple PHP Shopping Cart</h1>
     <!-- Display Message -->
    <?php if (isset($message)): ?>
        <p><strong><?php echo htmlspecialchars($message); ?></strong></p>
    <?php endif; ?>

    <!-- Product List -->
    <h3>Products:</h3>
    <ul>
        <li><a href="?add=Apple">Add Apple</a></li>
        <li><a href="?add=Banana">Add Banana</a></li>
        <li><a href="?add=Orange">Add Orange</a></li>
    </ul>
    <!-- View Cart -->
    <h3>Your Shopping Cart:</h3>
    <?php if (!empty($_SESSION['cart'])): ?>
        <ul>
            <?php foreach ($_SESSION['cart'] as $item): ?>
                <li><?php echo htmlspecialchars($item); ?></li>
            <?php endforeach; ?>
        </ul>
    <?php else: ?>
        <p>Your cart is empty.</p>
    <?php endif; ?>

    <!-- Clear Cart Link -->
    <p><a href="?clear=1">Clear Cart</a></p>

</body>
</html>

OUTPUT
Simple PHP Shopping Cart
Products:
Add Apple
Add Banana
Add Orange
Your Shopping Cart:
Your cart is empty.
Clear Cart
